                <head>The Democracy and Robt J. Walker</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Editorial condemning the Democratic press and alleging that Kansas Gov.
                    Walker is actually being groomed to succeed Buchanan in 1860.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>"The Friends of the South"</head>
                <origin>Richmond Enquirer</origin>
                <commentary>SS is pleased with the Enquirer for turning away from its championship
                    of "Southern Rights."</commentary>
                <excerpt>We have grown tired of the idle twaddle of the secessionists, about who are
                    "friends of the South" and who are not.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Expresses frustration with Southern extremism.</summary>
            </div>
